This paper deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on segmenting flooded buildings using satellite imagery, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data, making it relevant to graphics (cs.GR). The use of multiple sensors and temporal data also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) component to the paper. Finally, the application of this technology to disaster response and coordination suggests a potential relevance to robotics (cs.RO).
